senses.sense_definition: An acronym for "special educational needs", referring to the educational requirements of students who have learning difficulties or disabilities.

examples.text: The school has hired a new coordinator to manage the <w>SEN</w> department.
Teachers receive training to better support children with <w>SEN</w> in the classroom.

senses.sense_definition: A unit of currency used in Malaysia, Indonesia, and Cambodia, worth one hundredth of the main currency unit (ringgit, rupiah, or riel).

examples.text: The bus fare was only fifty <w>sen</w>, which was very affordable.
I found a ten <w>sen</w> coin on the street in Kuala Lumpur.

senses.sense_definition: A historical unit of Japanese currency worth one hundredth of a yen; no longer in circulation.

examples.text: In the early twentieth century, a few <w>sen</w> could buy a simple meal.
Collectors often look for the old fifty <w>sen</w> coin from the Meiji era.

senses.sense_definition: Oneself or yourself; used reflexively to refer to the person speaking or being addressed.

examples.text: You should keep that information to your <w>sen</w>.
He bought his <w>sen</w> a new pair of boots for the winter.

senses.sense_definition: A surname of Bengali or Khmer origin.

examples.text: Dr. <w>Sen</w> will be presenting her research at the conference tomorrow.
We are going to visit the <w>Sen</w> family this weekend.
